### Test Booking API - Simple 2-night stay
### This file can be used with VS Code REST Client extension or similar tools

### 1. Login first to get token
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@hotel.com",
  "password": "admin123"
}

### 2. Create a test room (requires token from step 1)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/rooms
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "roomNumber": "101",
  "type": "single",
  "pricePerNight": 1200
}

### 3. Test booking: 2-night stay (CORRECT ISO FORMAT)
### Expected: 2 nights × 1200 = 2400 ETB
POST http://localhost:5000/api/bookings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "roomId": "YOUR_ROOM_ID_HERE",
  "guestName": "Test Guest",
  "guestPhone": "+251911223344",
  "checkIn": "2026-07-01",
  "checkOut": "2026-07-03"
}

### 4. Test booking: 1-week stay (ISO FORMAT)
### Expected: 7 nights × 1200 = 8400 ETB
POST http://localhost:5000/api/bookings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "roomId": "YOUR_ROOM_ID_HERE",
  "guestName": "Week Stay Guest",
  "guestPhone": "+251922334455",
  "checkIn": "2026-07-10",
  "checkOut": "2026-07-17"
}

### 5. Test with wrong date format (SHOULD FAIL)
### This will be rejected by validation
POST http://localhost:5000/api/bookings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "roomId": "YOUR_ROOM_ID_HERE",
  "guestName": "Wrong Format Guest",
  "guestPhone": "+251933445566",
  "checkIn": "7/1/2026",
  "checkOut": "7/3/2026"
}

### 6. Get all bookings (to verify calculation)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/bookings
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
